	"keywords": "Robotics, Education, Educational Technology, Autism",
	"description": "In Spring 2018, I conducted a pilot study of a robot teaching sign language to\nchildren with autism. This blog post reflects on the results of the study, and\nour team’s process of designing the robot. \n\nRobotics, Sign Language, and Children with Autism\nTo start with, let’s answer the first big question: Why use a robot in autism\ntherapy? People with autism have an attention preference to objects over people\n[http://ekirjasto.kirjastot.fi/ekirjat/autismin-kirjo-ja-kuntoutus], and \nchildren with a",
	"headline": "I helped build a robot that teaches sign language to children with Autism. This is what I learned.",
